CNCP v1 22513
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#8838: v-memo support deep comparison of object",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:24:01.497784+00:00",
  "text": "v-memo support deep comparison of object\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\n\n```\r\n<div v-memo=\"[data]\">{{ data.time }}</div>\r\n```\r\nA property change in a deep object can't trigger update.\r\n\r\n```\r\n<div v-memo=\"[JSON.stringify(data)]\">{{ data.time }}</div>\r\n```\r\nJSON stringify is not a good idea, but I have to do.\r\n[demo](https://codesandbox.io/s/competent-maxwell-yrr7mf?file=/src/App.vue:22-62)\n\n### What does the proposed API look like?\n\nmaybe like this\r\n```\r\n<div v-memo.deep=\"[data]\">{{ data.time }}</div>\r\n```",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request"
  ],
